-Method Overriding: This can be established only with different classes having parent-child relationship
                  : This is also known as run time polymorphism

TOP CASTING and DOWN CASTING
- A class cannot have more than one parent class/ Multiple inheritance is not allowed through classes in Java[Diamond Problem]
- Down casting is not possible in Java. If we forcefully typecast a parent class into child class, at compile this
  will work but at runtime this action will throw ClassCastException
- method with final keyword cannot be overridden
- To stop inheritance of a class or to stop class from becoming parent of any other class, make the class final
- method with static keyword can be inherited but cannot be overridden
- method hiding is having same static method in both parent and child class and these methods are completely independent of each other.
- We can override and overloaded method [Yes]
- We can overload an overridden method as well [Yes]
- Override an overloaded static method [No]
- Overload an overridden static method [No]
- We can override from parents and grandParent as well.
-Multiple inheritance[Class with more than one parent] is not possible in Java among classes